---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProductCard from '../../components/ProductCard.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
import FAQSection from '../../components/FAQSection.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { products } from '../../data/products';

const uniformProducts = products.filter(p => p.category === 'volleyball-uniforms');

const faqs = [
  { question: 'What is included in a volleyball uniform set?', answer: 'A complete volleyball uniform set typically includes a jersey and matching shorts. Some teams also add libero jerseys, warm-up suits, and socks to form a complete kit. We can build any combination you need as a single coordinated order.' },
  { question: 'Do you offer NFHS-compliant volleyball uniforms for high school teams?', answer: 'Yes. Our high school volleyball uniforms are designed with NFHS compliance in mind, including proper number sizing, placement requirements, and permissible design elements. We review all high school orders against current NFHS guidelines.' },
  { question: 'Can college teams order NCAA-compliant uniforms?', answer: 'Absolutely. We are experienced with NCAA volleyball uniform regulations and can produce compliant uniforms for Division I, II, and III programs. We recommend sharing your conference\'s specific requirements when requesting a quote.' },
  { question: 'How do you handle different sizing within one team order?', answer: 'Every player on your roster can have a different size — that is completely standard for our team orders. You submit a size roster (player name + size per piece) and we produce each item to specification. Individual name and number customization is included.' },
  { question: 'Can I order matching libero uniforms with a different color?', answer: 'Yes. Libero uniforms in a contrasting or complementary color are a standard part of our volleyball uniform packages. We ensure the design elements and fonts remain consistent while differentiating the libero as required by rules.' },
  { question: 'What is the difference between a jersey and a full uniform?', answer: 'A jersey refers to the top garment only. A full volleyball uniform set includes both the jersey and matching shorts, sized and designed to coordinate. We offer both individual jerseys and complete uniform sets depending on your team\'s needs.' },
  { question: 'How far in advance should we order for the start of a season?', answer: 'We recommend placing your order 4–6 weeks before your first game. This allows time for design approval, production, and shipping with some buffer for any sizing adjustments. Rush production is available if you are closer to the season start date.' },  { question: 'How far in advance should I order volleyball uniforms before the season begins?', answer: 'Most teams order 5–7 weeks before their first game. Standard production runs 10–14 business days after design approval, with additional time needed for size collection and mockup review. For full multi-item packages including game uniforms, practice jerseys, and warm-ups, allow the full 7 weeks. Rush production is available for programs with tighter timelines.' },
  { question: 'Can I order a sample uniform set before committing to a full team order?', answer: 'Yes. Sample sets — jersey and shorts — are available for programs that want to verify fit, fabric quality, and color accuracy before their full roster order goes into production. Sample costs apply as a credit toward your full team order. Turnaround on samples follows standard production timing.' },
  { question: 'What happens if a player\'s uniform does not fit correctly upon delivery?', answer: 'We provide detailed size charts and recommend collecting actual body measurements rather than relying on self-reported clothing sizes. If a sizing issue results from a production error on our end, we replace the piece at no charge. If the issue stems from a measurement submitted by the program, we produce a replacement at cost with priority turnaround.' },
];

const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Volleyball Uniforms' },
];
import InlineQuoteSection from '../../components/InlineQuoteSection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Custom Volleyball Uniforms for Schools & Clubs | The Volleyball Uniforms"
  description="Order custom volleyball uniforms for high school, college, youth & club teams. Complete sets with jerseys & shorts. NFHS & NCAA compliant. Free mockups. Request a quote."
  canonical="https://thevolleyballuniforms.com/volleyball-uniforms/"
>
  <div class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-navy-950 to-electric-900 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">Custom Volleyball Uniforms for Schools, Colleges & Clubs</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-navy-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Complete volleyball uniform sets for high school programs, college teams, youth organizations, and competitive clubs. Every uniform is made to order with your colors, logo, and player details.</p>
        <a href="/request-a-quote/" class="btn-primary">Get a Quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Volleyball Uniform Collections</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle mx-auto">Shop by team type or customize a complete uniform set from scratch.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {uniformProducts.map(p => (
          <ProductCard name={p.name} slug={p.slug} image={p.images[0]} description={p.shortDescription} />
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 prose-custom">
      <h2>Complete Uniform vs. Jersey-Only: What Your Program Actually Needs</h2>
      <p>Many programs order jerseys and source shorts separately — or ask players to provide their own — and end up with visual inconsistency that undermines the professional appearance a uniform is supposed to create. A complete volleyball uniform set coordinates jersey and shorts in a single production run using the same color profile and design language, ensuring they match under gym lighting and read as a unified outfit rather than two separate garments worn together. Whether your program needs a jersey-only order (for programs that already have matching shorts in stock) or a complete jersey-and-shorts set, we produce both configurations. For programs building from scratch, complete sets are always the recommended approach. Browse all uniform types below or read on to understand how each configuration works.</p>

      <h2>How Jersey and Shorts Color Consistency Is Managed in Production</h2>
      <p>The most common sourcing mistake in volleyball uniform procurement is ordering jerseys and shorts from different suppliers or different production runs. Polyester sublimation color output depends on fabric dye lots, equipment calibration, and weave structure — all of which vary between suppliers and between production runs at the same supplier. Even when the same Pantone color is specified for both garments, visible color drift under gym lighting is common when the two pieces are not produced together. We manage color consistency across jersey and shorts by producing both pieces simultaneously in the same production session with the same color calibration. This is the only reliable way to guarantee they match. See our <a href="/women-volleyball-uniforms/">women's volleyball uniforms</a>, <a href="/men-volleyball-uniforms/">men's volleyball uniforms</a>, <a href="/youth-volleyball-uniforms/">youth volleyball uniforms</a>, <a href="/high-school-volleyball-uniforms/">high school volleyball uniforms</a>, and <a href="/college-volleyball-uniforms/">college volleyball uniforms</a> pages for program-specific details.</p>

      <h2>Governing Body Uniform Rules: High School, College, and Club</h2>
      <p>NFHS rules govern high school volleyball uniform requirements across most states, specifying minimum number dimensions (4-inch front, 6-inch back), color contrast requirements for numbers, libero jersey contrast standards, and permissible logo placement zones. NCAA and NAIA rules cover college programs with similar — but not identical — requirements on number placement, libero identification, and sponsor display. USAV and AAU rules apply to club programs with generally more permissive standards than the school-based governing bodies. When you submit a uniform order, we check your design against the relevant governing body's current rulebook as part of the standard mockup review process. Programs in states with NFHS amendments that differ from the base rulebook should share their state association's supplemental requirements at the time of order submission.</p>

      <h2>Build a Home and Away System From a Single Order</h2>
      <p>Most competitive volleyball programs — at the high school level and above — require visually distinct home and away uniform configurations. The host team typically wears its primary color scheme (dark jersey, dark shorts or light jersey, light shorts depending on program identity), and the visiting team wears the alternate. Ordering both configurations simultaneously in a single production run is significantly more cost-efficient than ordering them in separate runs at different times, and guarantees that the design language is perfectly consistent between home and away versions. We recommend specifying both configurations from the start of the design consultation so the home and away design relationship is intentional rather than retrofitted. Contact us about dual-configuration pricing for programs ordering both home and away sets together.</p>

      <h2>What's Included in a Full Volleyball Uniform Set</h2>
      <p>A full volleyball uniform set includes a sublimated game jersey and matching shorts — both produced with the same design, same colors, and same player personalization (name and number) for every player on the roster. Most competitive programs also add a libero jersey in a contrasting colorway as a mandatory competition item. Programs that want a complete apparel system extend the set with <a href="/volleyball-warm-up-suits/">warm-up suits</a> for sideline and travel wear, <a href="/volleyball-practice-jerseys/">practice jerseys</a> for daily training use, and <a href="/volleyball-socks/">custom team socks</a> for a head-to-toe coordinated look. All of these can be ordered together as part of a <a href="/volleyball-team-kits/">volleyball team kit</a> for the best combined pricing and a single design consultation that covers every piece.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FAQSection faqs={faqs} title="Volleyball Uniforms FAQs" />
  <InlineQuoteSection />

  <CTASection title="Design Your Team's Uniforms Today" subtitle="Get a free mockup and quote for complete custom volleyball uniform sets within 1–2 business days." />
</BaseLayout>
